<subSubSection id="52BB49D6FF95FF84B68BF96BA7E9F8E2" pageId="3" pageNumber="238" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="1A1E1A5DFF95FF84B68BF96BA7E9F8E2" blockId="3.[174,1232,1727,1850]" pageId="3" pageNumber="238">
Diagnosis. This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="DDA161DEFF95FF84B4C4F914A74DF901" baseAuthorityName="Rossi" baseAuthorityYear="1790" box="[684,824,1727,1753]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Perithous" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="divinator">
<emphasis id="28D5C64FFF95FF84B4C4F914A74DF901" box="[684,824,1727,1753]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="238">P. divinator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but has the second tergite with a distinct median longitudinal keel anteriorly (
<figureCitation id="829A06D8FF95FF84B4A2F90BA753F921" box="[714,806,1759,1786]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[166,199,1766,1788]" captionTargetBox="[272,1126,1043,1744]" captionTargetId="figure-372@4.[272,1126,1043,1744]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Perithous spp.: 1 — P. speculator, female, habitus, lateral view; 2 — P. scurra, female, dorsal view of the second metasomal tergite; 3–4 — dorsal view of propodeum and metasomal tergites I–II, female: 3 — P. divinator; 4 — P. septemcinctorius; 5 — P. scurra, male, habitus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454728" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454728/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="238">
fig. 2, 
<emphasis id="28D5C64FFF95FF84B570F90BA753F921" box="[792,806,1759,1785]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="238">2</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
) and longer ovipositor (about 4.5– 5.0 × length of hind tibia). Flight period in Carpathians. May to August (19.05–10.08).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
